README-Sales Summary with SQLite & Python

Overview

This project demonstrates how to connect Python to an SQLite database to fetch basic sales data, summarize it, and visualize results using a bar chart.

Features

Connects to sales_data.db SQLite database.

Executes SQL queries to calculate:

Total quantity sold per product.

Total revenue per product.


Displays summary in the console.

Plots a simple bar chart of revenue by product.


Tools

Python (sqlite3, pandas, matplotlib)

SQLite (no installation needed)

Jupyter Notebook or Python script


Usage

1. Run the Python script/notebook.


2. View the printed sales summary.


3. Check the bar chart of revenue by product.



Learning Outcome

Writing SQL queries in Python.

Importing SQL data into pandas.

Summarizing data.

Visualizing sales data withÂ matplotlib.
